.TH "ubifs_evict_xattr_inode" 9 "ubifs_evict_xattr_inode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubifs_evict_xattr_inode \- Evict an xattr inode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ubifs_evict_xattr_inode
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "ino_t xattr_inum "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "xattr_inum" 12
xattr inode number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When an inode that hosts xattrs is being removed we have to make sure
that cached inodes of the xattrs also get removed from the inode cache
otherwise we'd waste memory. This function looks up an inode from the
inode cache and clears the link counter such that \fBiput\fP will evict
the inode.
